      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Industry Applications</h2>
        <div class="application-tags">
          <span>Backlight Panel Production</span>
          <span>Display Manufacturing</span>
          <span>Optical Film Processing</span>
          <span>LCD Assembly</span>
        </div>
      </section>


      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Application Scenarios</h2>
        <div class="scenario-list">
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>LCD Backlight Unit Assembly</h3>
            <p>Dust particles trapped between a backlight unit's diffuser sheet, light guide plate, or prism sheet cause bright spots and uniformity defects visible in the finished display. The Backlight Panel Cleaning Machine removes these particles immediately before assembly, significantly reducing the rework rate caused by contamination-induced optical defects.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Pre-Inspection Cleaning for Optical Films</h3>
            <p>Surface particles on backlight components cause false defect readings during automated optical inspection (AOI). Cleaning immediately before the inspection stage reduces false rejection rates, improves yield, and prevents the waste of reworking or discarding panels that have no genuine defects.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Display Component Preparation</h3>
            <p>Prism sheets, diffuser films, and reflector sheets that carry electrostatic charge actively attract airborne dust. The integrated static elimination system neutralizes this charge simultaneously with the adhesive roller cleaning, providing a dual-action surface preparation step for cleaner, more reliable display assembly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Why Adhesive Roller Cleaning for Backlight Components?</h2>
        <p>Backlight optical films are scratch-sensitive and cannot tolerate abrasive cleaning or solvent contact. Adhesive roller technology lifts and captures particles through gentle contact without scratching film surfaces, adding chemicals, or generating secondary contamination. Combined with the magnetic levitation drive system — which produces no friction particles of its own — the machine maintains the surface quality required for high-brightness display manufacturing.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block faq-block">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What types of backlight components can this machine clean?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The Backlight Panel Cleaning Machine handles backlight units, diffuser sheets, prism sheets, reflector sheets, and optical films used in LCD display manufacturing. Cleaning width is customized to match your production line's material size.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How does the integrated static elimination work?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The machine incorporates an intelligent static eliminator that neutralizes electrostatic charge on the film surface simultaneously with the adhesive roller cleaning pass. This prevents re-attraction of particles immediately after cleaning — a common problem when cleaning and static control are handled as separate steps.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Does the cleaning process scratch optical films?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">No. The adhesive roller cleaning method lifts particles from the surface through gentle, controlled contact without abrasives or solvents. The magnetic levitation drive system also ensures the transport mechanism itself generates no particles or vibration that could cause surface marks.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What is the quick-change window structure?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The quick-change window structure allows the adhesive roller to be replaced or cleaned without disassembling the machine enclosure. This minimizes production downtime during maintenance and roller changes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can the machine be integrated into an existing production line?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. The Backlight Panel Cleaning Machine is designed for inline integration. Cleaning width and conveyor specifications are customizable to match your existing line layout. Contact us with your line specifications for a tailored configuration.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What power supply does the machine require?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The machine operates on 220V / 50Hz. For other voltage requirements, please contact us during the quotation stage.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

